    "body": "If `blockwise` supported multiple output arrays directly, we could use it to implement `xarray.map_blocks`, instead of needing to write our own custom Dask graph manipulation:\r\nhttps://github.com/pydata/xarray/blob/e6791852aa7ec0b126048b0986e205e158ab9601/xarray/core/parallel.py#L164-L589\r\n\r\nThis also feels like the right basic \"primitive\" operation for implementing most distributed array operations.\r\n\r\n`blockwise` is the low-level routine used for implementing `apply_gufunc` and `map_blocks`, so this would presumably be a broadly useful building block and would subsume https://github.com/dask/dask/issues/72",
